TY  - JOUR
T1  - Investor Psychology and Asset Pricing
Y1  - 2001/08/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/08/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/0022-1082.00379
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 1533
EP  - 1597
VL  - 56
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/0022-1082.00379
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - The basic paradigm of asset pricing is in vibrant flux. The purely rational approach is being subsumed by a broader approach based upon the psychology of investors. In this approach, security expected returns are determined by both risk and misvaluation. This survey sketches a framework for understanding decision biases, evaluates the a priori arguments and the capital market evidence bearing on the importance of investor psychology for security prices, and reviews recent models.
ER  - 

